    <h3>What is climbing?</h3>
    <p>Climbing is a physically and mentally demanding sport that involves ascending natural 
        or artificial structures using strength, technique, and endurance. It comes in various forms, 
        including rock climbing, bouldering, sport climbing, and mountaineering, each requiring different 
        skills and equipment. Climbers rely on grip strength, balance, and problem-solving abilities to navigate 
        routes, often using ropes, harnesses, or protective gear for safety. The sport challenges both body and mind, 
        promoting fitness, resilience, and strategic thinking while offering the thrill of conquering heights and exploring 
        new terrains.</p>

